				<div class = "project-descrip">
					<h3>
						Urgent Call lets users silence their phone, eliminate distraction, and still be reached when needed most.
					</h3>
					<p>
						Urgent Call allows people to put their phone into silent mode, but still receive alerts if they receive 3 calls from the same person in less than 15 minutes, or get a text message with the phrase "Urgent!" embedded in it. Alert triggers are customizable, can be filtered by contact, and users can add new alert rules to tailor the alerts to different situations.
					</p>
					<p>
						Primary learnings from this project include:
					</p>
					<ul>

						<li>Careful evaluation of tradeoffs between form and function to keep the user interface clean and simple, yet filled with enough customization to satisfy most users</li>
						<li>Continuous design review to make the interface simpler and more intuitive based on personal intuition, observation and feedback from users, and study of the Android Design documentation</li>
						<li>Storing preferences in lists and databases as appropriate, and storing in a way that is accessible and easy to upgrade as features are added</li>	
						<li>Using helper functions to access preference data, making code more maintainable as data structures change</li>
						<li>Frequent code refactorization to keep the codebase managable and maintainable</li>	
					</ul>

					<p>
						Keeping a clean and simple interface was a critical concern for this project, especially since most users will rarely change the alert settings after the first time. To demo some of this progress, screenshots and package files of older iterations are included below.
					</p>
